label.value: date of FFPE slide review by the pathologist

definition.value: A data item that reports the calendar date when a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) slide was reviewed by a pathologist.

label.value: name of data entry person for local pathology review form

definition.value: A personal name that designates the person who performed the data entry process for filling in a local pathology review form.

label.value: presence of sarcomatoid features on specimen slide

definition.value: An information content entity that is an indicator of whether examination of a tissue specimen slide revealed the presence of sarcomatoid features.

label.value: sarcomatoid features observed on FFPE slide

definition.value: A textual entity that describes sarcomatoid features observed on a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) slide.

label.value: name of person in gross room receiving OR specimen

definition.value: A personal name that designates the person who received a specimen in a pathology gross room from an associated operating room (OR).

label.value: specimen transport from OR to gross room SOP

definition.value: A specimen transport SOP governing the transport of tissue from the operating room (OR) to the pathology gross room.

label.value: specimen transport from OR to gross room was performed as per SOP

definition.value: An information content entity that is an indicator of whether transport of tissue from the operating room (OR) to the pathology gross room was performed in accordance with the relevant standard operating procedure (SOP).

label.value: specimen transport from OR to gross room issues or deviations from SOP

definition.value: A textual entity that describes issues with the transport of tissue from the operating room (OR) to the pathology gross room or deviations from the relevant standard operating procedure (SOP).

label.value: temperature in gross room when specimen arrived from OR

definition.value: A scalar measurement datum that is the output of a temperature measurement assay occurring in a pathology gross room and performed when a specimen arrived from the operating room (OR).

label.value: humidity in gross room when specimen arrived from OR

definition.value: A measurement datum that is the output of an assay of humidity occurring in a pathology gross room and performed when a specimen arrived from the operating room (OR).

label.value: name of performer of gross evaluation of resected tissue specimen

definition.value: A personal name that designates the person who performed the gross evaluation of a resected tissue specimen.

label.value: resected tissue specimen mass measurement datum

definition.value: A mass measurement datum that is the output of an assay to measure the weight of a resected tissue specimen.

label.value: gross appearance of disease in resected tissue

definition.value: An information content entity that is an indicator of whether gross appearance of disease was observed in a resected tissue specimen.

label.value: comment on gross evaluation of resected tissue specimen

definition.value: A textual entity that states information relevant to gross evaluation of a resected tissue specimen.

label.value: gross diagnosis of resected tissue

definition.value: A diagnosis that is based on the gross evaluation of a resected tissue specimen.

label.value: photograph of tissue was taken in pathology gross room

definition.value: An information content entity that is an indicator of whether a photograph was taken in the pathology gross room of a resected tissue specimen.

label.value: reason for not taking a photograph of resected tissue in pathology gross room

definition.value: A textual entity that describes the reason no photographs were taken of a resected tissue specimen in the pathology gross room.

label.value: pathology ink used on resected tissue specimen

definition.value: An information content entity that is an indicator of whether pathology ink was used to mark the resected tissue specimen.

label.value: ink used for marking surgical margin

definition.value: A processed material that is used to mark the margin of a surgical excision of a resected tissue. It is used to evaluate whether the margin is free of tumor tissue.

label.value: tumor tissue was released to the biobank

definition.value: An information content entity that is an indicator of whether a tumor tissue specimen was released to a biobank.

label.value: explanation of why tumor tissue specimen was not released to a biobank

definition.value: A textual entity that describes the reason why a tumor tissue specimen was not released to a biobank.

label.value: percentage of gross area of necrosis of a specimen sent to biobank

definition.value: A data item that is the result of determining the percentage of gross area of necrosis of a specimen sent to a biobank.

label.value: percentage of tumor content of specimen sent to biobank

definition.value: A data item that is the result of determining the percentage of tumor content of a specimen sent to a biobank.

label.value: second piece of tumor tissue was collected

definition.value: An information content entity that is an indicator of whether a second piece of tumor was collected and released to a biobank.

label.value: dimensions of each specimen meet the criteria specified within the relevant tissue procurement SOP

definition.value: An information content entity that is an indicator of whether the dimensions of each specimen meet the criteria specified within the relevant tissue procurement standard operating procedure (SOP).

label.value: comment on deviations in specimen dimensions from a tissue procurement SOP

definition.value: A textual entity that states information relevant to deviations from a tissue procurement SOP with regards to specimen dimensions.

label.value: normal adjacent tissue released to the biobank in addition to tumor tissue

definition.value: An information content entity that is an indicator of whether normal adjacent tissue was released to the biobank in addition to the tumor tissue.

label.value: time of specimen transfer from pathology gross room to a biobank

definition.value: A data item indicating the time when a specimen was transferred from a pathology gross room to a biobank.

label.value: no recurrence of tumor

definition.value: An information content entity that is about the status of a tumor and indicates that there has not been a recurrence.

label.value: follow-up on donor outcome comment from tissue procurement

definition.value: A comment from tissue procurement that was submitted as part of a follow-up documenting donor outcome after initial specimen collection.

label.value: participant signed and dated informed consent form

definition.value: An information content entity that is an indicator of whether the participant signed and dated a specified informed consent form.

label.value: specimen collection quality review comment

definition.value: A textual entity that states information relevant to a review to determine if requirements were met for a specimen collection from a donor.

label.value: minimum required pre-operative RNA and DNA PAXgene tubes were collected

definition.value: An information content entity that is an indicator of whether the minimum required pre-operative RNA and DNA PAXgene tubes were collected from a donor.

label.value: desired plasma and serum aliquots were obtained

definition.value: An information content entity that is an indicator of whether the desired plasma and serum aliquots were obtained from a specimen donor.

label.value: top priority tumor specimen was obtained and processed with a particular FFPE fixation delay protocol

definition.value: An information content entity that is an indicator of whether a tumor specimen was obtained and processed with a particular FFPE fixation delay protocol to meet the top priority for tissue procurement.

label.value: additional tumor specimen was obtained and processed with a particular FFPE fixation delay protocol

definition.value: An information content entity that is an indicator of whether a tumor specimen was obtained and processed with a particular FFPE fixation delay protocol other than meeting the top priority for tissue procurement.

label.value: local pathology review of QC FFPE tumor tissue H&E slide was completed

definition.value: An information content entity that is an indicator of whether the local pathology review of a hematoxylin (H&E) slide derived from a quality control (QC) formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) tumor tissue was completed.

label.value: local pathology review was consistent with site of tissue procurement diagnostic pathology report

definition.value: An information content entity that is an indicator of whether the local pathology review was consistent with the findings of the diagnostic pathology report from the site of specimen collection from a donor.

label.value: specimen donor clinical data entry was completed

definition.value: An information content entity that is an indicator of whether clinical data entry was completed for a specimen donor.

label.value: tumor specimen satisfied criteria of necrosis percentage and tumor content

definition.value: An information content entity that is an indicator of whether the tumor specimen obtained satisfied criteria of necrosis percentage and tumor content of tumor cells by surface area.

label.value: all requirements for an investigation are met enabling release of specimen for shipment.

definition.value: An information content entity that is an indicator of whether all requirements for an investigation were met such that a specimen from a particular donor is released for shipment.

label.value: activity related to a particular specimen donor was stopped.

definition.value: An information content entity that is an indicator of whether activity related to a particular specimen donor was stopped.

label.value: activity related to a particular specimen donor was stopped because not enough blood collected

definition.value: An activity related to a particular specimen donor was stopped that is because there was not enough blood collected.

label.value: activity related to a particular specimen donor was stopped because not enough tissue

definition.value: An activity related to a particular specimen donor was stopped that is because there was not enough tissue.

label.value: activity related to a particular specimen donor was stopped because tissue was too necrotic

definition.value: An activity related to a particular specimen donor was stopped that is because the tissue was too necrotic.

label.value: activity related to a particular specimen donor was stopped because tissue was benign

definition.value: An activity related to a particular specimen donor was stopped that is because the tissue was benign.

label.value: activity related to a particular specimen donor was stopped because tissue was not released to a biobank

definition.value: An activity related to a particular specimen donor was stopped that is because the tissue was not released to a biobank.

label.value: research authorization for post mortem specimen donation

definition.value: An authorization in which a legally authorized individual is asked to give permission for general research for post mortem specimen donation from a person they represent.

label.value: research authorization obtainer role for post mortem donation of specimens from a legally authorized representative

definition.value: A role borne by a person who approaches a person's legal representative and informs them of key facts about potential risks and benefits, and asks them for authorization for post-mortem specimen donation  for general research for the person they legally represent.

label.value: research authorization documentation for post mortem specimen donation

definition.value: An authorization documentation that is the output of a research authorization for post mortem specimen donation.
